speech.p: The 668 bus from Cheddar village connects to the main service to Bristol, where several of its residents work. The cuts that have been made by Suffolk county council mean that the bus will end its journey in Shipham, leaving a 1.5 mile gap to Langford, which is across the county border. I have

remonstrated with the council, but it does not see that saving £14,000 annually on a bus service means that the taxpayer will have to support people who have to give up their jobs, even though they are able to work. Is there anything that the Leader of the House can do to help?
